  "prompt": "What is the salary of vlsi fresher in India?",
  "response": "As of 2023, the salary of a VLSI (Very Large Scale Integration) fresher in India typically ranges from \u20b93 to \u20b97 lakhs per annum, depending on various factors such as the company, location, and the candidate's educational background. \n\nTop-tier companies, especially in major tech hubs like Bangalore, Hyderabad, and Pune, may offer higher starting salaries, sometimes exceeding \u20b98 lakhs per annum for exceptionally skilled candidates. Additionally, candidates with internships or relevant project experience might command higher salaries.\n\nIt's important to note that these figures can vary and may change over time, so it's advisable to check current job listings and salary surveys for the most accurate information.",
